---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="How We Select Products and Brands"
  description="How Australian Home Collective chooses what to include in practical home and lifestyle guides."
>
  <header class="page-intro">
    <div class="narrow">
      <p class="eyebrow">How we choose what to include</p>
      <h1>How We Select Products and Brands</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        Our guides are designed to help with real home decisions. We focus on practical use,
        clear details and whether something makes sense for Australian households.
      </p>
    </div>
  </header>
  <section class="content narrow">
    <h2>What we look for</h2>
    <p>
      We look for products, brands and examples that help readers understand a category:
      practical use, clear specifications, Australian availability, transparent claims and
      suitability for everyday homes.
    </p>
    <h2>Useful comparison points</h2>
    <ul class="feature-list">
      <li>Whether the item solves a common household need.</li>
      <li>Whether claims are specific, supportable and easy for readers to verify.</li>
      <li>Whether materials, sizing, care instructions and limitations are clearly explained.</li>
      <li>Whether there are practical Australian considerations such as climate, delivery or standards.</li>
      <li>Whether the guide remains useful even if a particular item is unavailable.</li>
    </ul>
    <h2>What we avoid</h2>
    <p>
      We avoid vague claims, overcomplicated recommendations and items that only make sense in
      a narrow situation unless that limitation is clear. We also avoid making a guide feel like
      a long list when a smaller set of practical checks would be more useful.
    </p>
    <h2>How we update guides</h2>
    <p>
      We review guides when details change, when a topic needs clearer context or when reader
      feedback points out something that should be improved. Readers should still check current
      details directly with the relevant brand, service or professional before making decisions.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
